44:<A general remark: using $LaTeX$ will make your posts much more readable. :-)

The $phi$ in the last formula of your post should read $Z(z)$ I guess, at least that's what I see on the slide (edit: see you have fixed that now in your post). Now:


$T(t)(d^2 Z(z)/dz^2) + k^2phi(z,t) = T(t)(d^2 Z(z)/dz^2) + k^2Z(t)T(t) $.

So if  $T(t)(d^2 Z(z)/dz^2) + k^2Z(t)T(t)=0$ is follows (divide by $T(t)$) that

$d^2 Z(z)/dz^2 + k^2Z(t) = 0$, exactly what the slide says.>
