56:<I am presuming we are past that particular kind of freshman philosophy problem :) ! 

If you like, take the following more precise definition. Take the probability, per unit volume, of finding the particle within a small volume round about the point of interest. Take the limit of that quantity as the size of this volume is shrunk towards zero. If that is zero, then we will say the probability of finding the particle at that point is zero. If the wavefunction is zero, then the probability of finding the particle at that point will be said to be zero under this definition.>
