77:<I think if the the total Energy is less than the Potential energy you can't find the particle inside the barriers (Classical thinking) but from the quantum thinking point of view if V is much larger than E you will have very small probability of finding the particle inside the wall(barriers) (seems near the classical thinking) .. however if E is near to V the probability increase by tunneling effect (this has no analogue to classical thinking !!) ... same with the case of parabolic increasing Potential .. the most of our probability is to find the particle inside the distance where his total energy still over the potential energy (E> 0.5*K*z^2) and we where supposing that at the Energy = Potential point (classical turn out) this s the point we shouldn't find the particles after !! However there is also some tunneling happening for some distance and it was supposed that this particle don't exist at all after the classical turning point ;) ... check pages 42 and 43 of slides of particles in potential wells !!>
